The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 14 October is 4,173 (483 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 10 October, there were 367 new confirmed cases (42.5 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 03 October, there were 266 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 38% ( 101 extra cases).
